Camila and Carlos have no business working with customers. Carlos has been at this location for 3 months but does not know how to make the subs. Camila, stay off the register if you do not know how to use it. Management, who was in charge 2:30p-3:00p 3/6/2019? They need to be replaced. A line wrapping around into the dinning area at this time is unacceptable. There is a young male that has been at this location for quite a while (well over a year I would say) quickly found something needing tending in the back area leaving the inexperienced staff to fend for themselves with 10 or more guests in line is not the right thing to do. As for the older lady that I would assume was the lead worker there is no need to reprimand staff in front of customers. Yes, Carlos messed up a couple sandwiches back to back but that is a reflection of management not doing their jobs not a reason to verbally chastise him in front of customers. I left with half of what I came for and honestly I could not continue waiting (more than 20 minutes) for Camila to figure out what cookies the customer wanted after he clearly said it 3 times. It will be a very very long time till I consider coming back to this location and that will be merely because of convenience. Hopefully by the time I decide to come back the revolving door of employees will have brought in fresh batch.
